2. That in this body or humane nature, he should be a Servant §. 15. or yeild obedience; hence God calls him his Servant, Isa. 42. 1. Behold my Servant whom I uphold; & that this was also in the condition prescribed to him, our Saviour acknowledges▪ Isa. 49. 5. Now saith the Lord that formed me from the womb to be his Servant;
And in pursuit hereof, Christ takes upon him the forme of a servant Phil.
